fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph

Class Forest

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph.Forest

  • public class Forest
extends java.lang.Object

    A data forest is a data structure based upon a personal data graph. Among other things, building a spanning forest over a graph then allows to compute a radial layout of this graph very easily, even if it is not a tree, or it has several connected components.

    A Data Forest is actually a set of Data Trees (one per connected component of the graph). The way their roots are chosen is simple :

    • a main root is chosen by the user to be at the center of the layout and it is the root of the Data Tree over its connected component, which is designated main tree
    • For the other connected component, the vertex of smallest id is the root of the corresponding Data Tree.

      In this implementation, a map is stored to be able to determine to which tree a vertex belong. This allows to set any vertex as the new root of the Data Tree over its connected component easily and quickly.

      • minimizeCrossings

        public void minimizeCrossings(float vRadius,
                              Tree wTree,
                              RadialLayout wLayout,
                              Drawing wDrawing,
                              long maxTime)
                       throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        With specified time, places the forest in a state (i.e. permutes the children lists of its vertices) which minimizes the cost of the drawing of this forest with specified parameters.
        Parameters:
        vRadius - Required vertex Radius of the tree in percentage of the maximal allowed value, must be in ]0, 1[
        wTree - Working tree, previous content will be overwritten
        wLayout - Working layout, previous content will be overwritten
        wDrawing - Working drawing, previous content will be overwritten
        maxTime - Maximum time allocated to the minimization
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the vertex radius is out of bounds
